                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Profiles</th>
                        <td>S-Log3, S-Cinetone, HLG3</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Video Features</th>
                        <td>Active Stabilization, Focus Breathing Comp</td>
                    </tr>

                    <tr>
                        <th colspan="2" class="specs-group-header"
                            >Build & Connectivity</th
                        >
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Viewfinder</th>
                        <td>9.44M-dot OLED EVF (240fps)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Screen</th>
                        <td>3.2" 4-axis Vari-angle Touch (2.1M-dot)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Card Slots</th>
                        <td>Dual CFexpress Type A / SD UHS-II</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Ports</th>
                        <td>USB-C 3.2, HDMI 2.1 (Full Size), Audio In/Out</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Weather Sealing</th>
                        <td>Professional grade (dust & moisture)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Weight</th>
                        <td>650g (body only)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <a
                    href="#"
                    class="btn-buy"
                    rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer"
                    target="_blank"
                >
                    Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
                </a>
            </div>

            <div class="pros-cons">
                <div class="pros">
                    <h4>What We Like</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Outstanding 61MP image quality with excellent
                            dynamic range
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            True 8K 30p internal recording with oversampling
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Industry-leading AI autofocus with subject
                            recognition
                        </li>
                        <li>8 stops of IBIS for handheld versatility</li>
                        <li>
                            Dual CFexpress Type A slots for professional
                            reliability
                        </li>
                        <li>Improved 240fps EVF refresh rate</li>
                        <li>4K 120p for high-quality slow motion</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="cons">
                    <h4>Trade-offs</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Premium price point ($3,999) limits accessibility
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Large file sizes require significant storage
                            investment
                        </li>
                        <li>CFexpress Type A cards are expensive</li>
                        <li>Battery life moderate with 8K recording</li>
                        <li>
                            Rolling shutter present in electronic shutter mode
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Detailed Performance Section -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">In-Depth Performance</h2>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Image Quality & Resolution</h3>
                <p>
                    The 61-megapixel stacked sensor produces images with
                    exceptional detail and clarity. File sizes are substantial
                    (approximately 120MB raw files), but the payoff is
                    extraordinary cropping flexibility and large print
                    capability. The back-illuminated design ensures excellent
                    low-light performance despite the high pixel density.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Dynamic range is outstanding at base ISO, rivaling medium
                    format cameras in controlled lighting. The 14-bit raw files
                    capture subtle gradations perfectly, ideal for commercial
                    and landscape photography where maximum quality is
                    paramount.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Autofocus & Tracking</h3>
                <p>
                    Sony's latest AI-powered autofocus system sets a new
                    benchmark. The camera recognizes humans, animals, birds,
                    insects, vehicles, and trains with astonishing accuracy.
                    Real-time Eye AF works flawlessly even with erratic subject
                    movement, making it ideal for wedding photographers and
                    wildlife shooters.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The 759 phase-detection points cover 94% of the frame, with
                    tracking that sticks to subjects even when they temporarily
                    leave the frame. Focus acquisition speed is
                    near-instantaneous, and the system excels in challenging
                    backlit conditions.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
                <p>
                    The A7 V's 8K 30p recording is oversampled from the full
                    sensor width, delivering exceptional sharpness and color
                    accuracy. 4K footage benefits from 6K oversampling,
                    resulting in cleaner images with minimal aliasing. The 4K
                    120p mode enables high-quality slow-motion capture for
                    creative projects.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Heat management is impressive‚Äîcontinuous 8K recording is
                    possible for approximately 60 minutes in normal ambient
                    temperature. The camera includes active stabilization, focus
                    breathing compensation, and a full suite of professional
                    video tools including waveform monitor, zebras, and LUT
                    preview.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Build Quality & Ergonomics</h3>
                <p>
                    Sony has refined the A7 series ergonomics significantly. The
                    grip is deeper and more sculpted, providing excellent
                    handling even with large telephoto lenses. Button placement
                    is logical, and the addition of a dedicated photo/video/S&Q
                    switch streamlines workflow for hybrid shooters.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The 9.44 million dot EVF with 240fps refresh rate is among
                    the best available, providing a smooth, lag-free viewing
                    experience. The 4-axis vari-angle screen combines the
                    versatility of a flip-out design with the ability to quickly
                    position for vertical shooting.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Ideal Lenses -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Ideal Lenses for the Sony A7 V</h2>
            <div class="recommendations-grid">
                <div class="recommendation-card">
                    <h4>Sony FE 24-70mm f/2.8 GM II</h4>
                    <p>
                        The ultimate workhorse zoom. Exceptionally sharp across
                        the frame, resolves every bit of the 61MP sensor, and
                        features fast, silent autofocus. Perfect for events,
                        portraits, and general shooting.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="recommendation-card">
                    <h4>Sony FE 70-200mm f/2.8 GM OSS II</h4>
                    <p>
                        Flagship telephoto for sports, wildlife, and portrait
                        work. Outstanding optical quality, excellent
                        stabilization that complements the A7 V's IBIS, and
                        professional-grade build quality.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="recommendation-card">
                    <h4>Sony FE 35mm f/1.4 GM</h4>
                    <p>
                        Perfect for environmental portraits and low-light work.
                        The f/1.4 aperture creates gorgeous bokeh while
                        maintaining edge-to-edge sharpness. Compact enough for
                        travel yet built to professional standards.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="recommendation-card">
                    <h4>Sony FE 85mm f/1.4 GM</h4>
                    <p>
                        The portrait lens par excellence. Stunning bokeh,
                        clinical sharpness, and precise autofocus make it ideal
                        for studio and outdoor portraiture. Takes full advantage
                        of the A7 V's high resolution.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <section class="section faq-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Sony A7 V FAQ</h2>

            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">
                        How does the Sony A7 V compare to the A7 IV?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div
                        class="faq-answer"
                        style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;"
                    >
                        <p>
                            The A7 V offers significantly higher resolution
                            (61MP vs 33MP), 8K video capability (vs 4K 60p),
                            improved IBIS (8 stops vs 5.5 stops), and a better
                            EVF. The A7 IV remains an excellent choice for most
                            users, but the A7 V is for professionals who need
                            maximum resolution and advanced video features.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">
                        Is 8K video recording practical for most users?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div
                        class="faq-answer"
                        style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;"
                    >
                        <p>
                            8K is primarily useful for future-proofing content,
                            cropping flexibility in post, and delivering
                            oversampled 4K footage. It requires substantial
                            storage (approximately 200GB per hour) and powerful
                            editing hardware. For most users, the 4K modes offer
                            better balance between quality and workflow
                            efficiency.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">
                        What memory cards should I use with the A7 V?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div
                        class="faq-answer"
                        style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;"
                    >
                        <p>
                            For 8K recording and high-speed burst shooting,
                            CFexpress Type A cards with minimum 800MB/s write
                            speed are recommended. Sony's TOUGH series or
                            ProGrade Digital cards work excellently. For
                            photography-only workflows, high-speed UHS-II SD
                            cards (V90) are sufficient.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">
                        Does the Sony A7 V overheat during 8K recording?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div
                        class="faq-answer"
                        style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;"
                    >
                        <p>
                            Sony has made significant improvements to heat
                            management. The A7 V can record 8K continuously for
                            approximately 60 minutes at normal room temperature
                            before overheating. In Auto Temperature settings,
                            the camera manages heat intelligently. For extended
                            recording sessions, using an external recorder via
                            HDMI is recommended.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">
                        Who should buy the Sony A7 V?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div
                        class="faq-answer"
                        style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;"
                    >
                        <p>
                            The A7 V is ideal for professional photographers and
                            videographers who need maximum resolution, reliable
                            dual card slots, and cutting-edge video features.
                            It's perfect for commercial work, high-end
                            portraiture, landscape photography, and professional
                            video production. For enthusiasts or those primarily
                            shooting stills, the A7 IV or A7C II offer better
                            value.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Final Recommendation -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="final-verdict">
                <h2>Final Recommendation</h2>
                <p>
                    The Sony A7 V represents the pinnacle of hybrid camera
                    technology. It's not the camera for everyone‚Äîthe price point
                    and file sizes demand significant investment and workflow
                    consideration. But for professionals who need the absolute
                    best image quality, the most reliable autofocus, and
                    professional-grade video capabilities, it's an outstanding
                    choice.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Buy it if:</strong> You're a professional photographer
                    or videographer who needs maximum resolution, 8K capability, and
                    professional reliability.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Skip it if:</strong> You're on a budget, primarily shoot
                    stills, or don't need 8K video‚Äîthe A7 IV or A7C II offer better
                    value.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
<script is:inline src="/assets/js/faq-accordion.js"></script>
</BaseLayout>
